msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.49:0.2"
msgid "5. Mahāyaññavagga"
msgstr "5. A Great Sacrifice"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 49. Dutiyasaññāsutta → vitthanasattasaññāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.49:0.3"
msgid "49. Dutiyasaññāsutta"
msgstr "49. Perceptions in Detail"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.49:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sattimā, bhikkhave, saññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā "
"amatogadhā amatapariyosānā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these seven perceptions, when developed and cultivated, are "
"very fruitful and beneficial. They culminate in the deathless and end with "
"the deathless."

msgctxt "an7.49:1.2"
msgid "Katamā satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "an7.49:1.3"
msgid ""
"Asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā, "
"aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā."
msgstr ""
"The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness of food, dissatisfaction "
"with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, and not-self "
"in suffering."

msgctxt "an7.49:1.4"
msgid ""
"Imā kho, bhikkhave, satta saññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti "
"mahānisaṃsā amatogadhā amatapariyosānāti."
msgstr ""
"These seven perceptions, when developed and cultivated, are very fruitful "
"and beneficial. They culminate in the deathless and end with the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.49:2.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asubhasaññā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā "
"amatogadhā amatapariyosānā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When the perception of ugliness is developed and cultivated it’s very "
"fruitful and beneficial. It culminates in the deathless and ends with the "
"deathless.’"

msgctxt "an7.49:2.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an7.49:2.3"
msgid ""
"Asubhasaññāparicitena, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cetasā bahulaṃ viharato "
"methunadhammasamāpattiyā cittaṃ patilīyati patikuṭati pativattati, na "
"sampasāriyati upekkhā vā pāṭikulyatā vā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant often meditates with a mind reinforced with the perception "
"of ugliness, their mind draws back from sexual intercourse. They shrink "
"away, turn aside, and don’t get drawn into it. And either equanimity or "
"revulsion become stabilized."

# daddula is unclear. Comm has cammanillekhana, but why should we abandon the word nharu, which is clear?
msgctxt "an7.49:2.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kukkuṭapattaṃ vā nhārudaddulaṃ vā aggimhi pakkhittaṃ "
"patilīyati patikuṭati pativattati, na sampasāriyati."
msgstr ""
"It’s like a chicken’s feather or a strip of sinew thrown in a fire. It "
"shrivels up, shrinks up, rolls up, and doesn’t stretch out."

msgctxt "an7.49:2.5"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asubhasaññāparicitena cetasā bahulaṃ "
"viharato methunadhammasamāpattiyā cittaṃ patilīyati patikuṭati pativattati, "
"na sampasāriyati upekkhā vā pāṭikulyatā vā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant often meditates with a mind reinforced "
"with the perception of ugliness, their mind draws back from sexual "
"intercourse. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: anusandahati → anusandati (bj, s2, s3, pts1) | anusaṇṭhāti (si)
msgctxt "an7.49:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sace, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asubhasaññāparicitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharato "
"methunadhammasamāpattiyā cittaṃ anusandahati appaṭikulyatā saṇṭhāti;"
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant often meditates with a mind reinforced with the perception of "
"ugliness, but their mind is drawn to sexual intercourse, and not repulsed,"

# On pubbenapara, see BB’s note. I don’t think it quite means “successive stages”, here or elsewhere. In all the contexts i’ve seen, it fits with the meaning of “as compared to how it was before”. See DN 26: Tassa samatena janapadaṃ pasāsato pubbenāparaṃ janapadā na pabbanti, yathā taṃ pubbakānaṃ rājūnaṃ ariye cakkavattivatte vattamānānaṃ. Also note the reading bhavanaphala found in PTS without variants, while here text says bhavanabala, also without variants.
msgctxt "an7.49:3.2"
msgid ""
"veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā ‘abhāvitā me asubhasaññā, natthi me "
"pubbenāparaṃ viseso, appattaṃ me bhāvanābalan’ti."
msgstr ""
"they should know: ‘My perception of ugliness is undeveloped. I don’t have "
"any distinction higher than before. I haven’t attained a fruit of "
"development.’"

msgctxt "an7.49:3.3"
msgid "Itiha tattha sampajāno hoti."
msgstr "In this way they are aware of the situation."

msgctxt "an7.49:3.4"
msgid ""
"Sace pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asubhasaññāparicitena cetasā bahulaṃ "
"viharato methunadhammasamāpattiyā cittaṃ patilīyati patikuṭati pativattati, "
"na sampasāriyati upekkhā vā pāṭikulyatā vā saṇṭhāti;"
msgstr ""
"But if a mendicant often meditates with a mind reinforced with the "
"perception of ugliness, their mind draws back from sexual intercourse …"

msgctxt "an7.49:3.5"
msgid ""
"veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā ‘subhāvitā me asubhasaññā, atthi me "
"pubbenāparaṃ viseso, pattaṃ me bhāvanābalan’ti."
msgstr ""
"they should know: ‘My perception of ugliness is well developed. I have "
"realized a distinction higher than before. I have attained a fruit of "
"development.’"

msgctxt "an7.49:3.6"
msgid "Itiha tattha sampajāno hoti."
msgstr "In this way they are aware of the situation."

msgctxt "an7.49:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘Asubhasaññā, bhikkhave, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā "
"amatogadhā amatapariyosānā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘When the perception of ugliness is developed and cultivated it’s very "
"fruitful and beneficial. It culminates in the deathless and ends with the "
"deathless.’ "

msgctxt "an7.49:3.8"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

